Indonesian President Joko Widodo, known among the people as Jokowi, promised to address these inequalities and human rights violations in Papua in his 2014 election campaign.
The former carpenter won 27 of the 29 constituencies in Papua, including Pania, on his way to the presidential palace in Jakarta.
