The Institute issued 581 test results in May and said 442 cases “have indications that the person under investigation is 18 years of age or older.”
But when the Svenska Dagbladet newspaper examined the results of their 581 tests, it turned out that in 243 cases a person had directly claimed to be 18 this year.
