The rules aimed at preventing the unbridled spending of European football clubs do not prevent Neymar’s world record transition from the Spanish football club to the Paris-Saint Germain in Barcelona, France.
Any consequences from UEFA, the governing body that governs the European game, and which has the power to ban teams from participating in the prestigious Champions League tournament, are still ahead of Paris Saint-Germain.
The financial rules for fair play (FFP) established by UEFA in 2011 mean that PSG will have to at some point prove that the Neymar transition was financed without huge losses.
